=> In Memory Authentication

	- We will be using  InMemoryUserDetailsManager class which implements UserDetailsManager, UserDetailsPasswordService
	- It manages Users n Memory( Non-persistent implementation of UserDetailsManager which is backed by an in-memory map.) no DB needed
	- InMemoryUserDetailsManager has constructor which takes UserDetails(I) in built class object. UserDetails implemented by User class implements UserDetails, CredentialsContainer
	
		public InMemoryUserDetailsManager(UserDetails... users) {
		for (UserDetails user : users) {
			createUser(user);
		}
	}
	
	- password("{noop}password1") : It means no encoding for password..if we are using any encoding we can provide algorithm
	
